lient  and company value partner with engineering user experience and release teams to continually build and deliver worldclass products with predictable highquality product releases support strategic planning across engineering to ensure alignment with corporate company and client strategies objectives and goals responsible and accountable for the daytoday leadership and execution of the product management team while effectively balancing resource demands of product development with core system infrastructure improvements manage flawless and timely execution of development projects and enhancements including prioritization integration scope and deadlines resource allocation etc provide product management expertise on corporate and company initiatives to ensure we are using the best possible technologies to achieve state of the art seamless and scalable solutionsmust haves  bachelor’s degree in related field  years relevant work experience building and scaling products and enhancements  years’ managing and scaling product management teams  years’ directdigital marketing experience experience in evaluating and coordinating technical requirements product design and architecture and value proposition roi analysis for technology solutions history of establishing the right technology solutions and processes that are reliable maintainable and scalable in fastpaced growing and ambiguous environments experience in leading and evaluating user experience and design implications for products successful track record of improving product management processes and driving engineering improvements including continuous integration and deployment techniques demonstrated ability to align define and leverage clear measurable departmental and individual performance goals system architecture chops across both hardware and softwareeven better  advanced degree desire to build and improve technologies and processes and drive synergies ability to establish trust build relationships and influence people at all levels of the organization interest in a newly created position with the opportunity to shape and scope accountabilities has experience managing user experience and design functionabout education advisory boardeab is a best practices firm that uses a combination of research technology and services to improve the performance of  educational institutions headquartered in washington dc eab forges and finds the best new ideas and proven practices from its network of thousands of leaders then customizes and hardwires them into every level of member organizations creating enduring value for more information visit wwweabcom  we are a workplace that     values and celebrates diversity of experience culture and opinion     is committed to creating an inclusive environment to enhance our collective experience     promotes a supportive community through staffled affinity groups events and education​our culture  values we think forbes said it best “making the world a better place is what the advisory board company is all about” we have a unique culture where employees are told to avoid after work emails encouraged to take  hours per month of paid leave for community service and are expected to add surplus value in every interaction with a member or colleague  over the past thirty years we have developed a distinctive corporate culture based on our values and principles we award promote and praise based on individual performance capabilities and ambition we provide ways for staff to share their time talent and passions in the community we reward innovation and foster a collaborative environment we have a performancedriven staff and peers that challenge one another in the workplace and we want freethinkers agile speakers witty writers and team players to join the firm – at advisory board your ideas are heard and your contributions matter perks a few of manyconsistent with our belief that our employees are our most valuable resource the advisory board company of