l and communication skills high adaptability strong domain expertise as well as an entrepreneurial mindset and product management skills this individual is primarily responsible for creating a distinctive product vision managing the multiyear product roadmap and creating an effective engineering partnership to deliver a marketleading solution this is a unique opportunity to lead a growing team within the health care technology organization and work with the most progressive health systems in the country the director of product management will report to the vp product management for health care technology and will work closely with the general manager strategy lead and development team for the customerpatient experience domain the position is based out of our washington dc office what youll be doing  collaborate with internal and external stakeholders to create a distinctive product vision for an analytic platform to improve the endtoend patient experience omnichannel marketing and customer acquisition strategies  translate product vision into an executable roadmap for the core product and continue to refine product vision over time based on feedback from users domain experts and the market  own the success against product and business kpis working in concert with business owners  partner with ux strategy product design and data science colleagues to lead product discovery usability and user research workshops to ensure that we are building high value usable and desired features  partner with data science colleagues to apply advanced analytic techniques such as predictive and prescriptive modeling eg sentiment propensity segmentation clustering retention persistencychurn longterm profitability etc  translate market analysis user feedback and competitive analysis into the agile development process ie user stories annotated wireframes etc  oversee the development backlog prioritizing new features enhancements and defects against clear business priorities  oversee the rollout of predictable highquality product releases  collaborate with commercial colleagues on product gotomarket strategy and support the commercial pipeline as presales technical and domain expert  provide internal and external stakeholders with the appropriate updates on progress vision product roadmap etc must haves   education bachelors degree   years of professional experience delivering software products   years of product management experience for a consumer software product or service  proven experience managing a high performing team of  direct reports  demonstrable understanding of crm technology and customer experience   demonstrable understanding of the sdlc and agile methodologies  experience with consumer products or digital strategy  proven ability to manage a complex array of internal and external stakeholders  proven ability to boil down market findings into new productenhancement ideas even better     years of enterprise software product management experience in health it   years of data science or machine learning experience  bachelor’s degree in a life science or physical science computer science mathematics engineering or related degree program   masters degree in business health carerelated field computer science mathematics informatics or related degree program  proven ability to lead product discovery or other usercentric development techniques  proven track record managing and mentoring more junior product managers about advisory board advisory board is a best practices firm that uses a combination of research technology and consulting to improve the performance of  health care organizations headquartered in washington dc with offices worldwide advisory board forges and finds the best new ideas and proven practices from its network of thousands of leaders then customizes and hardwires them into every level of member organizations creating enduring value for more information visit wwwadvisorycom     we are a workplace that      values and cel